President Joseph R. Biden Jr. has sent a notice to Congress stating that the national emergency with respect to the situation in or in relation to the Democratic Republic of the Congo will continue beyond October 27, 2023. The situation in the Democratic Republic of the Congo, characterized by widespread violence and atrocities that threaten regional stability, is deemed an unusual and extraordinary threat to the foreign policy of the United States. Therefore, President Biden has determined it is necessary to extend the national emergency declared in Executive Order 13413, as amended by Executive Order 13671. The notice has been sent to the Federal Register for publication.